The paper deals with the problem of embedding four-directional and three-directional paths on a set of points in the plane, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. The paper also provides a complete picture of the problem for convex point sets, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves the study of planar embeddings, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also involves the use of labels and directions, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
